detail.name: Beater Grabs the Snitch
detail.text: Return a Match in play to its owner's hand
detail.flavorText: 'Harry learnt that there were seven hundred ways of committing a Quidditch foul...'

detail.name: Bulgeye Potion
detail.text: You may use an Action and discard this card from play to do 13 damage to your opponent.

detail.name: Christmas Feast
detail.text: Put up to 4 non-Healing Item cards from your discard pile into your hand.
detail.flavorText: 'Harry had never in all his life had such a Christmas dinner.'

detail.name: Colour-Changing Ink
detail.text: You may use an Action to count the cards in your hand. Put them all on the bottom of your deck (in any order), and then draw that many cards.

detail.name: Draco Malfoy, Slytherin
detail.text: Once during each of your turns, when you use an Action to play an Item card, you get 1 more Action that turn.
detail.flavorText: 'My father's next door buying my books and mother's up the street looking at wands... Then I'm going to drag them off to look at racing brooms.' - Draco Malfoy

detail.name: Dragon-Hide Gloves
detail.text: Whenever a Creature does damage to you, prevent 1 of that damage.

detail.name: Eeylops Owl Emporium
detail.text: Each Owl has 1 more health. Whenever an Owl does damage, it does 1 more damage.
detail.flavorText: '...Eeylops Owl Emporium — Tawny, Screech, Barn, Brown and Snowy.' - Shop sign in Diagon Alley
detail.note: When you play this card, discard any other Location from play (yours or your opponent's).

detail.name: Flourish and Blotts
detail.text: Either player may use an Action and discard 2 of his or her Lessons from play to draw 5 cards.
detail.flavorText: 'They bought Harry's school books in a shop called Flourish and Blotts where the shelves were stacked to the ceiling...'
detail.note: When you play this card, discard any other Location from play (yours or your opponent's).

detail.name: Good Night's Sleep
detail.text: Choose 1 of your Characters in play that has a 'once per game' ability you have already used. Use that ability.
detail.flavorText: 'After a good night's sleep, Harry felt nearly back to normal.'

detail.name: Gringotts
detail.text: Each player gets 1 more Action on each of his or her turns (including the turn you play this card).
detail.flavorText: 'Enter stranger, but take heed of what awaits the sing of greed, ...' — Gringotts engraving
detail.note: When you play this card, discard any other Location from play (yours or your opponent's).

detail.name: Gringotts Vault Key
detail.text: Search your deck. You may take any card from your deck and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your deck
detail.flavorText: 'You have his key, sir?'' — Gringotts goblin

detail.name: Griphook
detail.text: Once per game, you may make your opponent discard his or her hand. Then your opponent draws as many cards as he or she discarded in this way.
detail.flavorText: ''If anyone but a Gringotts goblin tried that, they'd be sucked through the door and trapped in there,' said Griphook.''

detail.name: Gryffindor Match
detail.toSolve: Do 12 damage to your opponent while this card is in play. (That damage doesn't have to be done all at once.)
detail.reward: The winner gets 2 more Actions during his or her next turn.
detail.flavorText: ‘... this year's team is going to be brilliant.’ — Oliver Wood

detail.name: Hagrid, Keeper of Keys
detail.text: You may use an Action to search your deck. You may take a Location card from your deck, show it to your opponent and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your deck.
detail.flavorText: '...I haven't introduced meself. Rubeus Hagrid, Keeper of Keys and Grounds at Hogwarts' — Rubeus Hagrid

detail.name: Hagrid's Umbrella
detail.text: You may use an Action and discard this card from play to search your deck. You make take a Location card from your deck, show it to your opponent and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your deck. If you play this card, and you already have a Wand in play, discard the old one.

detail.name: Hebridean Black Dragon
detail.text: To play this card, discard 1 of your Care of Magical Creatures Lessons from play.
detail.flavorText: ''But there aren't wild dragons in Britain?' said Harry.'

detail.name: Hedwig
detail.text: When you play this card, you may put a non-Healing card from your discard pile into your hand.
detail.flavorText: 'He had decided to call her Hedwig, a name he had found in A History of Magic.'

detail.name: Hermione, Top Student
detail.text: Once per game, you may search your deck. You may take up to 2 Lesson cards from your deck, show them to your opponent and put them into your hand. Then shuffle your deck.
detail.flavorText: '...Hermione, of course, came up top of the year.'

detail.name: Lee Jordan
detail.text: You may use an Action to reveal the top 3 cards of your deck. Put all of those cards that need Quidditch Power into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your deck (in any order).
detail.flavorText: 'The Weasley twins' friend, Lee Jordan, was doing the commentary for the match, ...'

detail.name: Letters From No One
detail.effect: Your opponent may only use Actions to draw cards.
detail.toSolve: Your opponent discards 5 cards from his or her hand.
detail.reward: Your opponent may draw two cards.
detail.flavorText: '...thirty or forty letters came pelting out of the fireplace like bullets.'

detail.name: Madam Irma Pince
detail.text: You may use an Action to put a Book card from your discard pile into your hand. (Lesson cards aren't Books.)
detail.flavorText: 'Madam Pince the librarian brandished a feather duster...'

detail.name: Professor Quirinus Quirrell
detail.text: Once per game, you may return all Creatures and Items to their owners' hands.
detail.flavorText: 'Even Professor Quirrell was temblin' ter meet yeh — mind you, he's usually tremblin'.' — Rubeus Hagrid

detail.name: Self-Stirring Cauldron
detail.text: To play this card, discard 2 of your Potions Lessons from play. You get 1 more Action the turn you play this card.

detail.name: Silver Unicorn Horn
detail.text: When you play this card, put up to 2 non-Healing cards from your discard pile on the bottom of your deck (in any order). You may use an Action and discard this card from play to shuffle up to 6 non-Healing cards from your discard pile into your deck.

detail.name: Table Trouble
detail.text: Discard all Items from play (yours and your opponent's).

detail.name: The Famous Harry Potter
detail.text: Before each of your turns, if there are 4 or fewer cards in your hand, you may draw a card.
detail.flavorText: 'I'm famous and I can't even remember what I'm famous for.' — Harry Potter

detail.name: The Leaky Cauldron
detail.text: Whenever either player plays a character card, he or she uses up 1 Action to play it instead of 2.
detail.flavorText: 'This is it,' said Hagrid, coming to a halt, 'the Leaky Cauldron. It's a famous place.'
detail.note: When you play this card, discard any other Location from play (yours or your opponent's).

detail.name: Three-Month-Long Match
detail.toSolve: Do 30 damage to your opponent while this card is in play. (That damage doesn't have to be done all at once.)
detail.reward: The winner does 15 damage to his or her opponent.
detail.flavorText: 'A game of Quidditch... can go on for ages...' — Oliver Wood

detail.name: Through the Arch
detail.effect: Your opponent can't play Spell cards.
detail.toSolve: Your opponent skips a total of 4 Actions. (Those Actions don't need to be one right after the other.)
detail.reward: Your opponent may put an Item card from his or her discard pile into his or her hand.
detail.flavorText: 'Welcome,' said Hagrid, 'to Diagon Alley.'

detail.name: Vanishing Referee
detail.text: Choose a non-Healing Character in play (other than a starting Character) and shuffle it into its owner's deck.
detail.flavorText: '...referees had been known to vanish and turn up months later in the Sahara Desert.'

detail.name: Alihotsy Draught
detail.text: Do 6 damage to your opponent or choose 1 of his or her Items in play and discard it.

detail.name: Barn Owl
detail.text: When you play this card, you may discard 1 of your Care of Magical Creatures Lessons from play to put a Creature card from your discard pile into your hand.

detail.name: Beetle Eyes
detail.text: When you play this card, do 4 damage to your opponent. You may use an Action to discard this card and Eel Eyes from play to search your deck. You may take a Bulgeye Potion card from your deck and put it into play. Then shuffle your deck.

detail.name: Biased Commentary
detail.text: The next time this turn you play a Spell card that needs Quidditch Power, if that card does damage to your opponent, it does 5 more damage.
detail.flavorText: ''So — after that obvious and disgusting bit of cheating —' 'Jordan!' growled Professor McGonagall'

detail.name: Bluebottle Broom
detail.text: You may use an Action to put a non-Healing card from your discard pile on the bottom of your deck. If you play this card, and you already have a Broom in play, discard the old one.

detail.name: Cauldron Shop
detail.text: Either player may use an Action to search his or her deck. That player may take an Item card from his or her deck that needs Potions Power, show it to his or her opponent and put it into his or her hand. Then the player shuffles his or her deck.
detail.note: When you play this card, discard any other Location from play (yours or your opponent's).

detail.name: Colloshoo
detail.text: Look at your opponent's hand. If there are any Item cards there, choose 1 of them and discard it.

detail.name: Eel Eyes
detail.text: When you play this card, look at your opponent's hand. You may use an Action to discard this card and Beetle Eyes from play to search your deck. You may take a Bulgeye Potion card from your deck and put it into play. Then shuffle your deck.

detail.name: Frog-Spawn
detail.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to your Creatures.
detail.flavorText: 'I was the only one who saw her for what she was — a freak!' — Petunia Dursley

detail.name: Injured
detail.text: Look at your opponent's hand. Discard all cards from it that need Quidditch Power.

detail.name: Lapifors
detail.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Creatures in play and discard it. Then search your deck. You may take a Creature card from your deck, show it to your opponent and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your deck.

detail.name: Madam Malkin's Robes
detail.text: Whenever a card (yours or your opponent's) does damage, it does 1 less damage
detail.flavorText: 'Madam Malkin stood Harry on a stool… slipped a long robe over his head and started to pin it to the right length.'
detail.note: When you play this card, discard any other Location from play (yours or your opponent's).

detail.name: Porcupine Robe
detail.text: At the end of each of your opponent's turns, do 1 damage to each Creature that did damage to you that turn.

detail.name: Practical Joke
detail.text: Count the number of Items in play (yours and your opponent's). Do that much damage to your opponent.

detail.name: Quality Quidditch Supplies
detail.text: Either player may use an Action to search his or her deck. That player may take an Item card from his or her deck that needs Quidditch Power, show it to his or her opponent and put it into his or her hand. Then the player shuffles his or her deck.
detail.note: When you play this card, discard any other Location from play (yours or your opponent's).

detail.name: Spiral Dive
detail.text: Discard any number of cards from your hand. Do that much damage to your opponent
detail.flavorText: '...Harry streaked towards the ground like a bullet.'

detail.name: Verdillious
detail.text: Do 5 damage to your opponent or to a Creature of your choice.

detail.name: Wand Shop
detail.text: All Charms Lessons (yours and your opponent's) provide 2 Charms Lessons instead of 1 Charms Lesson.
detail.flavorText: '...Ollivanders: Makers of Fine Wands since 382 BC.' — shop sign in Diagon Alley
detail.note: When you play this card, discard any other Location from play (yours or your opponent's).

detail.name: Wild Boar
detail.text: To play this card, discard 2 of your Care of Magical Creatures Lessons from play.

detail.name: A Beginner's Guide to Transfiguration
detail.text: You may use an Action and discard this card from play to draw 3 cards.

detail.name: Bludger in the Stands
detail.text: Do 4 damage to your opponent. Then, if your opponent has any Items in play, he or she chooses 1 of them and discards it.

detail.name: Blue Wig
detail.text: Do 4 damage to your opponent. Then draw a card.
detail.flavorText: '...he'd somehow turned his teacher's wig blue.'

detail.name: Butterfly Weed Balm
detail.text: To play this card, discard 1 of your Potions Lessons from play. Shuffle up to 9 non-Healing cards from your discard pile into your deck.

detail.name: Cancelled Practice
detail.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Quidditch Lessons in play and discard it.
detail.flavorText: 'The snow still hadn't melted next morning.'

detail.name: Dogbane Potion
detail.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Creatures in play and do 3 damage to it.

detail.name: Dog Biscuits
detail.text: Remove all damage counters (if any) from 1 of your Creatures in play. Then draw a card.

detail.name: Fantastic Beasts & Where to Find Them
detail.text: You may use an Action and discard this card from play to draw 3 cards.

detail.name: Flipendo
detail.text: Do 2 damage to your opponent or to a Creature of your choice.
detail.flavorText: '...no magic should be used between classes in the corridors.' — Albus Dumbledore

detail.name: Freeze!
detail.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Creatures in play and do 4 damage to it.

detail.name: Magical Drafts and Potions
detail.text: You may use an Action and discard this card from play to draw 3 cards.

detail.name: Mid-air Collision
detail.text: Do 10 damage to your opponent. Then choose 1 of your cards in play (other than your starting character) and discard it.

detail.name: Moonseed Poison
detail.text: When you play this card, do 3 damage to your opponent. You may use an Action and discard this card from play to do 6 damage to your opponent.

detail.name: Picking on Neville
detail.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's cards in play (other than his or her starting character) and discard it. Your opponent may prevent this by choosing 2 of his or her cards in play (other than his or her starting character) and discarding them.
detail.flavorText: '...Neville managed to have an extraordinary number of accidents...'

detail.name: Pigley Dudley
detail.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Creatures or Characters in play (other than his or her starting character) and put it on top of his or her deck.
detail.flavorText: '...I suppose he was so much like a pig anyway there wasn't much left ter do.' — Rubeus Hagrid

detail.name: Quick Thinking
detail.text: Do 3 damage to your opponent or draw 3 cards.
detail.flavorText: '...Alicia Spinnet, a good friend of Oliver Wood's, last year only a reserve...'' — Lee Jordan, commentator

detail.name: Quidditch Through the Ages
detail.text: You may use an Action and discard this card from play to draw 3 cards.

detail.name: River Troll
detail.text: To play this card, discard 1 of your Care of Magical Creatures Lessons from play.
detail.flavorText: '...they're supposed to be really stupid,' said Ron.'

detail.name: Screech Owl
detail.text: When you play this card, you may put a Lesson card from your discard pile into your hand.

detail.name: Sloth Grip
detail.text: During your opponent's next turn, you may prevent all but the first 3 damage done to you.
detail.flavorText: '...that's Chaser Katie Bell of Gryffindor there…' — Lee Jordan, commentator

detail.name: Spongify
detail.text: Choose a non-Healing Item in play and return it to its owner's hand. Then draw a card.

detail.name: Swelling Potion
detail.text: Do 5 damage to your opponent. During your opponent's next turn, he or she can't use Actions to play Item cards.

detail.name: Tawny Owl
detail.text: When you play this card, you may put a non-Healing Item card from your discard pile into your hand.
detail.flavorText: 'All the kids want owls, they're dead useful...' — Rubeus Hagrid

detail.name: Teacup to Rat
detail.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Items in play and discard it. Then draw a card.
detail.flavorText: 'Oh, she... came home every holiday... turning teacups into rats.' — Petunia Dursley

detail.name: The Standard Book of Spells (Grade 1)
detail.text: You may use an Action and discard this card from play to draw 3 cards.

detail.name: Care of Magical Creatures
detail.text: Provides 1 Care of Magical Creatures lesson.

detail.name: Charms
detail.text: Provides 1 Charms lesson.

detail.name: Potions
detail.text: Provides 1 Potions lesson.

detail.name: Quidditch
detail.text: Provides 1 Quidditch lesson.

detail.name: Transfiguration
detail.text: Provides 1 Transfiguration lesson.
